  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the requirements to attend the Berkshire Hathaway Annual Shareholder Meeting?",
  "response": "To attend the Berkshire Hathaway Annual Shareholder Meeting, you must meet the following requirements:\n\n1. **Shareholder Status**: You must be a shareholder of Berkshire Hathaway. This means you need to own at least one share of either the Class A (BRK.A) or Class B (BRK.B) stock.\n\n2. **Meeting Credentials**: You will need to bring proof of ownership of your shares. This can be in the form of a brokerage statement or a letter from your broker confirming your ownership as of the record date, which is typically set a few weeks before the meeting.\n\n3. **Admission Ticket**: Shareholders will receive an admission ticket, which is usually mailed to them after they register for the meeting. You must bring this ticket with you to gain entry to the meeting.\n\n4. **Photo ID**: You will need to present a valid government-issued photo ID to verify your identity.\n\n5. **Registration**: You may need to pre-register for the meeting, either online or by mail, depending on the instructions provided by Berkshire Hathaway.\n\n6. **Arrival Time**: Plan to arrive early, as the meeting can attract a large number of attendees, and seating is typically on a first-come, first-served basis.\n\n7. **Dress Code**: There is no formal dress code, but business casual attire is common.\n\n8. **Age Requirement**: While there is no specific age requirement, attendees under the age of 18 must be accompanied by an adult.\n\nIt's important to check the most current information and guidelines from Berkshire Hathaway's official website or communications, as requirements may change from year to year.",
